data.Project_Description:
(1) PROJECT BACKGROUND AND DESCRIPTION
The Business and R&D started investigation on expanding manufacturing footprint to MEA region and therefore contacted toller in Egypt to investigate possibilities of expanding production of Flexible Packaging portfolio there. 

(2) PROJECT SCOPE
Project scope defines the boundaries of a project. 
* "The proposed model is:
* Eagle to toll manufacture flexible packaging products in Egypt (with HBF brand & formulations)
* Start with 4 products 3 SL + 1 SB (SL 332, SL 312, XR 1300 and SBA 1010)
* Target around 100tons per month with significant growth potential
* Eagle to purchase RMs à produce the FGs à sell to HBF Egypt
* We are willing to accept Eagle selling to different HBF entities (ex.: HBF Dubai, South Africa, …), but will not accept Eagle to ship to customers directly"

(3) OBJECTIVES
Describe the high level objectives for the project including primary and secondary. 
PRIMARY OBJECTIVES:Localize 3SF and 1SB formulas in MEA region.
SECONDARY OBJECTIVES: make sure formulas are secured and protected.

(4) STAKEHOLDERS & KEY REPORTING RELATIONSHIPS
"List all that apply:
     Customer/client (internal/external)
     Project sponsor
     Project manager
     Other key team members
     Brief statements of key project reporting relationships"
Joe Tuso, Harsh Gupta, Anna Zieba, Mauel Ferreira, Dan Schulz, Nuno Malta, Andreas Meyer

(5) HIGH-LEVEL TIMELINE/SCHEDULE
Detail when the project will be completed and if they are a target or constraint.
Target Completion H1 2025

(6) EXPECTED TOTAL COST
Briefly describe the item(s) driving costs in this project that the stage holders 
Raw Material cots, Tolling Fee, Working Capital

(7) KEY CONSTRAINTS
Enter any constraints that will impact your project
Product quality comparing to Curitiba, Formula Security on toller side

(8) KEY ASSUMPTIONS
Enter any key assumptions. Examples of assumptions include but are not limited to new technology will work as planned, contracts or vendor will perform as expected, approvals can be obtained, problem CAN be solved.
n/a

(9) KEY CONCERNS/RISKS
Enter any identifiable and significant potential problem
Sharing formula with a "competitor"

(10) APPROVAL AND AUTHORITY TO PROCEED
We approve the project as described above, and authorize the team to proceed. 
"1. Joe Tuso
2. Anna Zieba
3. Ritu Paul"

Business reason to initiate a project?	Market Growth in MEA	
What is the problem we are going to solve?	Cost efficiency is preventing sucessful market penetration in MEA	
Key CTQs?	Match the performance and quality of the products in PIA / Curitiba	
Equipment Application	Standard FlexPack equipment	
Substrate	Standard FlexPack substrates	
Performance Criteria	quality matching products in PIA / Curitiba	
Environment	Standard FlexPack applications	
Any sustainability aspect?	Yes	
Project growth/defense ratio (total should be 100%)?	70%	Growth 	30%	Defense
